President Biden expressed condolences on behalf of the United States to Queen Elizabeth II and the people of the United Kingdom on what would have been Prince Philip's 100th birthday. He praised the British government's response and discussed his productive meeting with Prime Minister Johnson. They reaffirmed the Special Relationship between the US and the UK and discussed various issues such as cybersecurity, emerging technologies, global health, and climate change. They also talked about coordinating the withdrawal of troops from Afghanistan and leading the global fight against COVID-19. President Biden made a historic announcement that the US will purchase an additional half a billion doses of Pfizer's COVID-19 vaccine to donate to nearly 100 low- and lower-middle-income countries. He emphasized that the US is providing these vaccines with no strings attached and thanked Pfizer's CEO for his partnership. President Biden highlighted the importance of global cooperation in ending the pandemic and expressed commitment to continuing efforts to vaccinate the world.